---

## Matching Rule — Candidate Email Match

**Object:** Candidate__c  
**Match Criteria:** `Email__c` (Exact match)

### Metadata XML
```xml
<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>
<MatchingRule xmlns=\"http://soap.sforce.com/2006/04/metadata\">
    <fullName>Candidate_Email_Match</fullName>
    <booleanFilter>1</booleanFilter>
    <description>Match candidates by email</description>
    <label>Candidate Email Match</label>
    <matchingRuleItems>
        <fieldName>Email__c</fieldName>
        <matchingMethod>Exact</matchingMethod>
    </matchingRuleItems>
    <ruleStatus>Active</ruleStatus>
</MatchingRule>
```

---

## Matching Rule — Candidate Phone Match (Fuzzy)

**Object:** Candidate__c  
**Match Criteria:** `Phone__c` (Fuzzy match)

```xml
<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>
<MatchingRule xmlns=\"http://soap.sforce.com/2006/04/metadata\">
    <fullName>Candidate_Phone_Match</fullName>
    <label>Candidate Phone Match</label>
    <matchingRuleItems>
        <fieldName>Phone__c</fieldName>
        <matchingMethod>Exact</matchingMethod>
    </matchingRuleItems>
    <ruleStatus>Active</ruleStatus>
</MatchingRule>
```

---

## Duplicate Rule — Block Duplicate Candidates

```xml
<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>
<DuplicateRule xmlns=\"http://soap.sforce.com/2006/04/metadata\">
    <fullName>Block_Duplicate_Candidates</fullName>
    <actionOnInsert>Block</actionOnInsert>
    <actionOnUpdate>Block</actionOnUpdate>
    <alertText>A candidate with this email already exists.</alertText>
    <duplicateRuleMatchRules>
        <matchingRule>Candidate_Email_Match</matchingRule>
        <objectMapping>
            <inputObject>Candidate__c</inputObject>
            <outputObject>Candidate__c</outputObject>
        </objectMapping>
    </duplicateRuleMatchRules>
    <isActive>true</isActive>
    <masterLabel>Block Duplicate Candidates</masterLabel>
    <operationsOnInsert>Alert</operationsOnInsert>
    <operationsOnUpdate>Alert</operationsOnUpdate>
</DuplicateRule>
```

---

## Duplicate Rule — Warn on Duplicate Application

**Purpose:** If same Candidate applies to same Job twice, warn user.

```xml
<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>
<DuplicateRule xmlns=\"http://soap.sforce.com/2006/04/metadata\">
    <fullName>Warn_Duplicate_Application</fullName>
    <actionOnInsert>Allow</actionOnInsert>
    <actionOnUpdate>Allow</actionOnUpdate>
    <alertText>This candidate has already applied to this job.</alertText>
    <isActive>true</isActive>
    <masterLabel>Warn Duplicate Application</masterLabel>
    <operationsOnInsert>Alert</operationsOnInsert>
    <operationsOnUpdate>Alert</operationsOnUpdate>
</DuplicateRule>
```

---

## Test Scenarios

| # | Action | Expected |
|---|--------|----------|
| 1 | Create candidate with email `a@b.com` | Saved |
| 2 | Create another candidate with same email | Blocked with alert |
| 3 | Create candidate with similar phone | Alert shown |
| 4 | Same candidate applies to same job twice | Warning, allows save |

---

## Setup Path
**Setup → Data → Duplicate Management → Matching Rules → New**  
Then **Duplicate Rules → New** (referencing the matching rule).
